TY  - JOUR
T1  - An Integer Programming Algorithm for Portfolio Selection
AU  - Faaland, Bruce
Y1  - 1974/06/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.20.10.1376
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.20.10.1376
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1376
EP  - 1384
VL  - 20
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A mean-variance portfolio selection model suitable for the small investor is formulated as a sequence of quadratic integer programming problems. The special structure of these quadratic problems is exploited in a partial enumeration algorithm which uses cutting planes to accelerate convergence. Computational experience is reported on problems ranging in size from fifteen to fifty variables.
AB  - A mean-variance portfolio selection model suitable for the small investor is formulated as a sequence of quadratic integer programming problems. The special structure of these quadratic problems is exploited in a partial enumeration algorithm which uses cutting planes to accelerate convergence. Computational experience is reported on problems ranging in size from fifteen to fifty variables.
