TY  - JOUR
T1  - Surveillance Schedules for Medical Examinations
AU  - Kirch, R. L. A.
AU  - Klein, M.
Y1  - 1974/06/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.20.10.1403
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.20.10.1403
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1403
EP  - 1409
VL  - 20
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A model is developed to aid in determining examination schedules for the detection of an age-dependent disease. It is shown that in an optimal schedule the interval between examinations is proportional to the square root of the age-specific incidence probability of the disease. To illustrate the methodology, optimal schedules are developed for breast cancer examinations.
AB  - A model is developed to aid in determining examination schedules for the detection of an age-dependent disease. It is shown that in an optimal schedule the interval between examinations is proportional to the square root of the age-specific incidence probability of the disease. To illustrate the methodology, optimal schedules are developed for breast cancer examinations.
